column5: Lungs gave out at 4th km. Walked to recuperate then the sun showed itself helping me push it on the 5th km
Hips started hurting between 5th and 6th km then slowly became unbearable. 👋🏻 youth. Hopefully it’s just bad form or the old worn shoes
Running against the wind really sucks. Tried taking it easy for my hip but should’ve taken it even easier. Started feeling hip pain at about 1 - 1.5 km
Hip still hurts a bit. Took it easy to get back into it
Short and slow run with Chase
Very short morning ‘sprint’ after walking Chase
First 5K with Abi. Nice and chill to keep my hip good with no pain!

This was a tough one. Realised I went from exercising 3-4 days a week to nothing cause of covid and laziness.
Hip is feeling awesome so it’s time to get back into it! 💪🏼
Slowly though..
First 10K! Was aiming for 5:00/km, but still really happy with this
